        "creation_date": 1474797585,
        "body": "<p>HttpRequest  most time spends waiting for reply from server. For that time, thread releases the processor, so even if your application is provided with single core, multiple threads can run in parallel. You should care to occupy more than one core only if your application does intensive number computations. My suggestion is that you make Http Requests serially, and not in parallel, and this is the reason your application is not responsive.<\/p>\n",
